@node HELP_HISTORY
@title "AGASSM Help: AGASSM development history"
AGASSM was designed and created over several months with only my personal use in mind therefore, most of the features that I have added are ones that I myself find useful. Version numbers before v2.5 were incredibly basic and therefore I won't mention them.

v2.5 2/2/94   À Very basic using pictures only and was OS1.x compatible

v4.1 8/3/94   À Yes, lots of revisions including what I thought was OS2.0x
                and above but turned out to be OS3.x and above.
              À Complete code re-write from scratch.
              À Pictures, Animations and modules are catered for.
              À Background pictures could be used (thanks to a suggestion)
              À Very Large interface. (Really needed its own screen!)
              À Only one module per slideshow.
              À Sleep facility.

v4.5 24/3/94  À Cosmetic changes to GUI.
              À Lots of bug fixes.
              À Code was made modular for easier de-bugging and
                general tidiness.

v5.1 1/4/94   À More GUI changes.
              À Multiple modules in a single slideshow.
              À Yet more modularisation of code bringing a 20K
              À reduction in executable size!

v5.2 24/4/94  À ARexx interface added. (Test version only)

v5.3 25/4/94  À Bug fixes. Lots of them appeared after the ARexx module
                was added but were nothing to do with ARexx as such!

v5.4 14/6/94  À Pull down menus added giving the ability of keyboard
                shortcuts.

v5.6 11/7/94  À OS2.x requesters added (previously they were all my own
                code!)
              À Improved ARexx support (more commands!)

v5.9 29/7/94  À IFF Sample support added.
              À Defaults editor window added.
              À More ARexx improvements.

v6.1 11/8/94  À Keyfile protection added.
              À ARexx re-written with more commands also.

v6.2 4/12/94  À Wildcard support added to ARexx interface
                (Thanks for the autodocs info James)

v6.3 14/1/95  À Added a commodity port. AGASSM can be made to quit
                and hide from the Commodities Exchange program.

v6.4 14/7/95  À Minor bug fixes and a better event handling system.
                I sent this version to Amiganuts they said they would
                publish it and then they promptly folded!

v7.1 22/8/95  À (Test purposes only)
              À Totally re-designed GUI.
              À More changes to ARexx.
              À OS2.x+ rather than OS3.x+
              À I finally fixed the event handling bug in AGASSM!
              À Full list editing features (Add, Up, Down and Remove)

                This version went to F1 Licenceware and 5D Licenceware.
                5D said they liked it but could I add a few things....

v7.21 9/11/96 À Extra effects.
              À Better memory management.
              À CPU sensitive, changing the speed of the effects.
                BUT... No DMA slowdown. Hmmm :-(.
              À Basically all the prototype features of v7.22

Licenceware releases follow - Released through 5D Licenceware

v7.22 10/1/97 À PAL/NTSC mode switching removed due to Enforcer Hit.
              À Support for MED 'MMD1' module format (4-track only).
              À Modularised the more recent additions to AGASSM
                resulting in a 10k drop in executable size. This is
                counter-acted by use of different blitter techniques.
              À OCS, ECS and AGA support! (previously AGA only!)
              À Re-designed interface (altered/added windows)
              À Filetype recognition system
              À New fader routines
              À Better implementation of user defined macros
              À Now requires @{" ARexx " link HELP_PORTS} to access all features
              À Ability to alter sample playback rate
              À Standardised file format for slideshows. (SSM0)
              À Several Wipes now added.
              À Transparent support for @{" PowerPacked " link HELP_PACK} files
              À Several other major/minor bug fixes.
              À Virtual Memory support! (Tested with VMM v3.2)
              À Task checking to see if AGASSM is already running!
                (AGASSM does not like to run concurrently with itself!)
              À All Enforcer Hits removed! (All really stupid mistakes!)


v7.23 14/4/98 À Improved Filetype recognition system.
                AGASSM now recognises Normal/EHB and HAM6/8 IFF
                files automatically.
              À Full AGA monitor support with automatic ScreenMode change.
              À Force WB Monitor to override above feature.
              À CIA timers for ST module playback.
              À Variable speeds for effects.
              À Change to ARexx command list.
              À Better Overscan support.
              À New file format. (SSM1)
                SSM0 is still supported but only loading. All files are
                saved as SSM1.
              À More general bug fixes.
              À More accurate sample playback.
              À Re-tested Virtual Memory support with VMM v3.3!
              À Title Bar display improved.
              À Play Infinite slideshows ONCE ONLY in AGASSM.
              À Ability to merge slideshows added.
              À 250 object limit increased to 1000.
              À More effects featuring Wipe To..., Horiz Blinds and 4
                different spiral effects.
              À Major bug fix to picture load routine.
              À Improved File requester code.
                Remembers different paths and files for Load, Save and
                Merge. It also checks to see if a file already exists and
                if you want to overwrite it.
              À I have introduced the ability to move around super-bitmap
                screens. However, you must set the time limit for these
                screens to 'Mouse'. I.e. Wait for the left mouse button.
              À AGASSP v2.11 ARexx bug fix. ARexx didn't work with AGASSP
                v2.10! :-<. (Stupid mistake!)
@endnode

@node HELP_TROUBLE
@title "AGASSM Help: TroubleShooting"
Well, here it is! If you have any problems then I suppose the answer should be here. If you have a problem, and the answer is not here and you manage to solve it on your own then write it down and send it to me so that I can add it to this section or change the code to suit.

     Q À AGASSM appears to load but asks for the 'RexxMast' program.
         What is 'RexxMast' and where is it ?

     A À 'RexxMast' is a type of programming language that enables
         utilities to share and exchange information and also remotely
         control other tasks that are running. It can be found in the
         System drawer of your Workbench disk. AGASSM requires the use
         of ARexx for some of its operations and therefore will refuse
         to run fully unless 'RexxMast' has been activated and @{" ARexx " link HELP_PORTS} is
         present on the system.

     Q À I have an AGA machine but AGASSM says that only the ECS modes
         are available. Why is this?

     A À When AGASSM is first launched, it checks to see wether the Setpatch
         program has been run. If not, then the extra AGA features are
         not available to any OS friendly program. To enable AGA all you
         have to do is run the Setpatch command that is found in your
         'C:' directory and the re-run AGASSM. The about requester should
         now tell you that your current chipset is AGA.

     Q À Although some slider gadgets are not disabled, they don't work!

     A À This is because you have not selected an object at all or have
         not selected an object of the correct type!

     Q À AGASSM tells me that I have too many items in a @{" list " link HELP_LIST} when
         I try to add any more.

     A À This is because AGASSM only allows 1000 objects in a slideshow.
         Do you want more ? (2000, 3000, ... , n thousand)

     Q À AGASSM says it has found an Unknown Error. What is it?

     A À This is mainly for my testing purposes and you should never
         see this. If you do you may get a program reference name or
         a message to report this error to the author. In both cases
         I would ask that you inform me of all the details so that I
         can re-create the error so that I can eradicate it. Having
         said that I've not seen this error in ages but no program is
         100% error free. Even this one.

     Q À AGASSM is not using the effect when displaying one of the
         pictures in a slideshow, but AGASSP does. Why?

     A À This is a border line low memory scenario where AGASSM occupies
         more memory than AGASSP and in 2Mb or less machines, this is
         enough for AGASSM to run out of memory to carry out the effect
         so it just shows the picture instead. In really low memory
         situations, AGASSM does not even open a screen.

     Q À Sometimes, AGASSM and AGASSP corrupt the picture and the effects
         don't seem to work properly. What's happening?

     A À Well, it may be for many reasons such as memory fragmentation
         but I seem to think that this problem only occurs on accelerated
         machines :-(. For now, the solution is to turn off your CPU's data
         cache. (It works on my '030 after I switch it off!) In a future
         release, I hope to have it fixed for good. (How to slow the DMA,
         that is the question! (Any Ideas??))

     Q À Is there a way to quit from an infinite loop slideshow?

     A À Yes. It's a bit fiddly but I can't find any other way of doing
         it. Hold down both mouse buttons until you are returned to the
         WorkBench. Be patient however as it only works after a picture,
         anim, sample or ARexx script has been used.

     Q À When I use the speed slider to increase the speed of an effect,
         there is no change. Why?

     A À In the most part, this is down to processor power. Your main CPU
         is working at its limit and so, any increase in the slider will
         result in no speed increase. You need a faster processor to
         increase the speed any more!

     OR, The other reason is that because the slider is generic to all
         effects, some reach their maximum speed before others on the
         slider scale. If other effects are not affected by the first
         scenario then it is likely that you have reached the speed limit
         for that effect.

@{b}@{u}KNOWN BUGS...@{ub}@{uu} (well it's not really a bug, but...)

	With the introduction of the use of CIA timers for ST-Module playback, AGASSM now clashes with OctaMED as the both reserve the CIA timers for themselves. If you run AGASSM first, AGASSM can play modules, if OctaMED v5 is run first, it can play modules. OctaMEDPlayer v5.10 will crash if AGASSM is running!

    There is a problem in AGASSM which I can't do anything about as it is to do with badly formed MED modules. Some modules that can be used cause ENFORCER HITS!. It seems that Enforcer hits occur when a MED note is called that does not have a sample associated with it.

    The solution is to edit out the notes that do not have a sample associated with them using OctaMED.

@endnode

